        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 3:28AM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 328 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Two Buttes Reservoir, or 14 miles northwest of
Springfield, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Springfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
